<TITLE> Derailed goods van disrupts Dhaka-Sylhet rail link </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com)The Dhaka-Sylhet rail link has been severed after a goods train partially derailed at Bhanugach Station near Srimangal Saturday night. A single wagon of the train, on its way to Chatok from Shaestaganj, derailed at 8.45pm, Srimangal stationmaster Md Jahangir Alam told bdnews24.com. Alam said: "Two wheels of a wagon came off the track between the home and outer signal of Bhanugach Station." A tool van had departed from Sylhet at 10.15pm, he said, adding it would take two hours to reach Bhanugach. bdnews24
